
  GLOSSARY

  task - a message passing finite state machine.

  task ID - a non-negative, non-zero integer enumerated in [app]/host.h

  internal message - an 8-byte internal communication.

  external message - a message between two or more hosts via the two wire
                     interface.

  process - an end-to-end cooperation of tasks governed by a director.

  director - a task that governs a process.

  secretary - a task that extends the functionality of a server,
              typically providing a network slave to job translation.

  client - a task requesting a service.

  server - a task providing a service.

  execution window - the time taken by a task to process a message.
